66],{"type":25,"value":767},"默认启用robots.txt: 控制搜索引擎爬虫行为。",{"type":16,"tag":187,"props":769,"children":771},{"id":770},"结论",[772],{"type":25,"value":770},{"type":16,"tag":21,"props":774,"children":775},{},[776],{"type":25,"value":777},"Nuxt 3代表了Vue全栈开发的一个重大飞跃。通过全面拥抱Vue 3、引入Vite、改进TypeScript支持、简化开发体验等一系列创新,Nuxt 3为开发者提供了构建现代、高性能Web应用的强大工具集。无论是小型项目还是大规模应用,Nuxt 3都能提供出色的开发体验和运行时性能。",{"type":16,"tag":21,"props":779,"children":780},{},[781],{"type":25,"value":782},"随着Nuxt 3的不断成熟和生态系统的扩展,我们可以期待看到更多基于Nuxt 3的创新应用和解决方案。对于Vue开发者来说,现在正是深入学习和采用Nuxt 3的最佳时机,以充分利用这个强大框架带来的所有优势。",{"title":8,"searchDepth":153,"depth":153,"links":784},[785,789,793,797,801,805,809,813,817],{"id":228,"depth":153,"text":231,"children":786},[787,788],{"id":239,"depth":67,"text":242},{"id":269,"depth":67,"text":269},{"id":292,"depth":153,"text":292,"children":790},[791,792],{"id":302,"depth":67,"text":305},{"id":331,"depth":67,"text":331},{"id":359,"depth":153,"text":362,"children":794},[795,796],{"id":370,"depth":67,"text":373},{"id":394,"depth":67,"text":397},{"id":437,"depth":153,"text":437,"children":798},[799,800],{"id":447,"depth":67,"text":447},{"id":494,"depth":67,"text":494},{"id":535,"depth":153,"text":538,"children":802},[803,804],{"id":546,"depth":67,"text":546},{"id":564,"depth":67,"text":564},{"id":598,"depth":153,"text":601,"children":806},[807,808],{"id":609,"depth":67,"text":609},{"id":627,"depth":67,"text":630},{"id":654,"depth":153,"text":654,"children":810},[811,812],{"id":664,"depth":67,"text":664},{"id":703,"depth":67,"text":703},{"id":721,"depth":153,"text":724,"children":814},[815,816],{"id":732,"depth":67,"text":735},{"id":751,"depth":67,"text":754},{"id":770,"depth":153,"text":770},"content:1.writings:nuxt3-features.md","1.writings/nuxt3-features.md","1.writings/nuxt3-features",{"_path":822,"_dir":6,"_draft":7,"_partial":7,"_locale":8,"title":823,"description":824,"published":825,"tags":826,"body":828,"_type":157,"_id":1024,"_source":159,"_file":1025,"_stem":1026,"_extension":162},"/writings/vue-composition-api","深入理解Vue 3 Composition API","探索Vue 3 Composition API的强大功能和使用方法","2024/03/18",[211,213,172,827],"Composition API",{"type":13,"children":829,"toc":1009},[830,835,840,846,851,857,862,868,886,891,902,908,927,931,941,952,956,966,975,980,985,990,999,1004],{"type":16,"tag":176,"props":831,"children":833},{"id":832},"深入理解vue-3-composition-api",[834],{"type":25,"value":823},{"type":16,"tag":21,"props":836,"children":837},{},[838],{"type":25,"value":839},"Vue 3的发布带来了许多激动人心的新特性,其中最引人注目的莫过于Composition API。这个新的API为我们提供了一种更灵活、更强大的方式来组织和重用组件逻辑。本文将深入探讨Composition API的核心概念、使用方法以及它如何改变我们的Vue开发体验。",{"type":16,"tag":187,"props":841,"children":843},{"id":842},"什么是composition-api",[844],{"type":25,"value":845},"什么是Composition API?",{"type":16,"tag":21,"props":847,"children":848},{},[849],{"type":25,"value":850},"Composition API是Vue 3引入的一个新的API集合,旨在解决Vue 2中Options API的一些限制。它允许我们使用导入的API函数来描述组件逻辑,而不是依赖于预定义的组件选项。这种方法提供了更好的代码组织、逻辑重用和类型推断。",{"type":16,"tag":187,"props":852,"children":854},{"id":853},"为什么需要composition-api",[855],{"type":25,"value":856},"为什么需要Composition API?",{"type":16,"tag":21,"props":858,"children":859},{},[860],{"type":25,"value":861},"在大型复杂的应用中,Options API可能会导致组件变得难以理解和维护。相关的逻辑可能分散在不同的选项中,使得代码难以追踪和重构。Composition API通过允许我们按照逻辑关系组织代码,解决了这个问题。",{"type":16,"tag":187,"props":863,"children":865},{"id":864},"setup函数composition-api的入口",[866],{"type":25,"value":867},"setup函数:Composition API的入口",{"type":16,"tag":21,"props":869,"children":870},{},[871,877,879,884],{"type":16,"tag":56,"props":872,"children":874},{"className":873},[],[875],{"type":25,"value":876},"setup",{"type":25,"value":878},"函数是Composition API的核心。它在组件创建之前执行,作为组合逻辑的入口点。在",{"type":16,"tag":56,"props":880,"children":882},{"className":881},[],[883],{"type":25,"value":876},{"type":25,"value":885},"中,我们可以定义响应式状态、计算属性、方法等,并将它们返回以供模板使用。",{"type":16,"tag":130,"props":887,"children":889},{"id":888},"setup函数的基本结构",[890],{"type":25,"value":888},{"type":16,"tag":48,"props":892,"children":897},{"className":893,"code":895,"language":896,"meta":8},[894],"language-vue","\u003Ctemplate>\n  \u003Cdiv>\n    \u003Cp>Count: {{ count }}\u003C/p>\n    \u003Cp>Double Count: {{ doubleCount }}\u003C/p>\n    \u003Cbutton @click=\"increment\">\n      Increment\n    \u003C/button>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/template>\n\n\u003Cscript setup>\nimport { computed, onMounted, ref } from 'vue'\n// 响应式状态\nconst count = ref(0)\n// 计算属性\nconst doubleCount = computed(() => count.value, 2)\n// 方法\nconst increment = () => {\n  count.value++\n}\n// 生命周期钩子\nonMounted(() => {\n  console.log('组件已挂载')\n})\n\u003C/script>\n","vue",[898],{"type":16,"tag":56,"props":899,"children":900},{"__ignoreMap":8},[901],{"type":25,"value":895},{"type":16,"tag":187,"props":903,"children":905},{"id":904},"响应式系统的核心ref和reactive",[906],{"type":25,"value":907},"响应式系统的核心:ref和reactive",{"type":16,"tag":21,"props":909,"children":910},{},[911,913,919,920,926],{"type":25,"value":912},"Composition API引入了两个主要的响应式API:",{"type":16,"tag":56,"props":914,"children":916},{"className":915},[],[917],{"type":25,"value":918},"ref",{"type":25,"value":582},{"type":16,"tag":56,"props":921,"children":923},{"className":922},[],[924],{"type":25,"value":925},"reactive",{"type":25,"value":590},{"type":16,"tag":130,"props":928,"children":929},{"id":918},[930],{"type":25,"value":918},{"type":16,"tag":21,"props":932,"children":933},{},[934,939],{"type":16,"tag":56,"props":935,"children":937},{"className":936},[],[938],{"type":25,"value":918},{"type":25,"value":940},"用于创建一个响应式的引用,可以包含任何类型的值",{"type":16,"tag":48,"props":942,"children":947},{"className":943,"code":945,"language":946,"meta":8},[944],"language-javascript","import { ref } from 'vue'\nconst count = ref(0)\nconsole.log(count.value) // 0\ncount.value++\nconsole.log(count.value) // 1\n","javascript",[948],{"type":16,"tag":56,"props":949,"children":950},{"__ignoreMap":8},[951],{"type":25,"value":945},{"type":16,"tag":130,"props":953,"children":954},{"id":925},[955],{"type":25,"value":925},{"type":16,"tag":21,"props":957,"children":958},{},[959,964],{"type":16,"tag":56,"props":960,"children":962},{"className":961},[],[963],{"type":25,"value":925},{"type":25,"value":965},"用于创建一个响应式对象,可以包含多个属性",{"type":16,"tag":48,"props":967,"children":970},{"className":968,"code":969,"language":946,"meta":8},[944],"import { reactive } from 'vue'\nconst state = reactive({ count: 0 })\nconsole.log(state.count) // 0\nstate.count++\n",[971],{"type":16,"tag":56,"props":972,"children":973},{"__ignoreMap":8},[974],{"type":25,"value":969},{"type":16,"tag":187,"props":976,"children":978},{"id":977},"计算属性和监听器",[979],{"type":25,"value":977},{"type":16,"tag":130,"props":981,"children":983},{"id":982},"计算属性",[984],{"type":25,"value":982},{"type":16,"tag":21,"props":986,"children":987},{},[988],{"type":25,"value":989},"计算属性是根据其他响应式状态计算得出的值。它们在模板中使用,但不会在响应式数据流中引入新的响应式状态。",{"type":16,"tag":48,"props":991,"children":994},{"className":992,"code":993,"language":946,"meta":8},[944],"import { computed, ref } from 'vue'\nconst count = ref(0)\nconst doubleCount = computed(() => count.value, 2)\nconsole.log(doubleCount.value) // 0\ncount.value++\nconsole.log(doubleCount.value) // 2\n",[995],{"type":16,"tag":56,"props":996,"children":997},{"__ignoreMap":8},[998],{"type":25,"value":993},{"type":16,"tag":130,"props":1000,"children":1002},{"id":1001},"监听器",[1003],{"type":25,"value":1001},{"type":16,"tag":21,"props":1005,"children":1006},{},[1007],{"type":25,"value":1008},"监听器用于监听响应式状态的变化,并在变化时执行某些操作。",{"title":8,"searchDepth":153,"depth":153,"links":1010},[1011,1012,1013,1016,1020],{"id":842,"depth":153,"text":845},{"id":853,"depth":153,"text":856},{"id":864,"depth":153,"text":867,"children":1014},[1015],{"id":888,"depth":67,"text":888},{"id":904,"depth":153,"text":907,"children":1017},[1018,1019],{"id":918,"depth":67,"text":918},{"id":925,"depth":67,"text":925},{"id":977,"depth":153,"text":977,"children":1021},[1022,1023],{"id":982,"depth":67,"text":982},{"id":1001,"depth":67,"text":1001},"content:1.writings:vue-composition-api.md","1.writings/vue-composition-api.md","1.writings/vue-composition-api",{"_path":1028,"_dir":6,"_draft":7,"_partial":7,"_locale":8,"title":1029,"description":1030,"published":1031,"body":1032,"_type":157,"_id":1236,"_source":159,"_file":1237,"_stem":1238,"_extension":162},"/writings/building-your-first-api-with-expressjs-a-beginners-guide","Building Your First API with Express.js: A Beginner's Guide","A beginner-friendly guide to building your first API with Express.js","2023/11/2",{"type":13,"children":1033,"toc":1225},[1034,1041,1047,1052,1058,1063,1068,1079,1084,1090,1095,1104,1110,1115,1124,1129,1135,1140,1149,1155,1160,1165,1174,1189,1195,1200,1206,1211,1216,1220],{"type":16,"tag":17,"props":1035,"children":1036},{},[1037],{"type":16,"tag":21,"props":1038,"children":1039},{},[1040],{"type":25,"value":26},{"type":16,"tag":187,"props":1042,"children":1044},{"id":1043},"what-is-expressjs",[1045],{"type":25,"value":1046},"What is Express.js?",{"type":16,"tag":21,"props":1048,"children":1049},{},[1050],{"type":25,"value":1051},"Express.js is a minimal and flexible Node.js web application framework that provides a robust set of features to develop web and mobile applications. It facilitates the rapid development of Node-based web applications and is widely used to build APIs due to its simplicity and performance.",{"type":16,"tag":187,"props":1053,"children":1055},{"id":1054},"step-1-setting-up-your-environment",[1056],{"type":25,"value":1057},"Step 1: Setting Up Your Environment",{"type":16,"tag":21,"props":1059,"children":1060},{},[1061],{"type":25,"value":1062},"Before you start, ensure that you have Node.js installed on your system. You can download it from Node.js official website.",{"type":16,"tag":21,"props":1064,"children":1065},{},[1066],{"type":25,"value":1067},"Once Node.js is installed, you can initiate your project:",{"type":16,"tag":48,"props":1069,"children":1074},{"className":1070,"code":1072,"language":1073,"meta":8},[1071],"language-bash","mkdir my-express-api\ncd my-express-api\nnpm init -y\n","bash",[1075],{"type":16,"tag":56,"props":1076,"children":1077},{"__ignoreMap":8},[1078],{"type":25,"value":1072},{"type":16,"tag":21,"props":1080,"children":1081},{},[1082],{"type":25,"value":1083},"This creates a new directory for your project and initializes a new Node.js project.",{"type":16,"tag":187,"props":1085,"children":1087},{"id":1086},"step-2-installing-expressjs",[1088],{"type":25,"value":1089},"Step 2: Installing Express.js",{"type":16,"tag":21,"props":1091,"children":1092},{},[1093],{"type":25,"value":1094},"Install Express.js using npm (Node Package Manager):",{"type":16,"tag":48,"props":1096,"children":1099},{"className":1097,"code":1098,"language":1073,"meta":8},[1071],"Copy code\nnpm install express --save\nThis command installs Express.js and adds it to your project's dependencies.\n",[1100],{"type":16,"tag":56,"props":1101,"children":1102},{"__ignoreMap":8},[1103],{"type":25,"value":1098},{"type":16,"tag":187,"props":1105,"children":1107},{"id":1106},"step-3-creating-your-first-express-server",[1108],{"type":25,"value":1109},"Step 3: Creating Your First Express Server",{"type":16,"tag":21,"props":1111,"children":1112},{},[1113],{"type":25,"value":1114},"Create a file named app.js in your project directory. This file will be the entry point of your API. Add the following code to app.js:",{"type":16,"tag":48,"props":1116,"children":1119},{"className":1117,"code":1118,"language":53,"meta":8},[51],"const express = require('express')\nconst app = express()\nconst port = 3000\n\napp.get('/', (req, res) => {\n  res.send('Hello World!')\n})\n\napp.listen(port, () => {\n  console.log(`Example app listening at http://localhost:${port}`)\n})\n",[1120],{"type":16,"tag":56,"props":1121,"children":1122},{"__ignoreMap":8},[1123],{"type":25,"value":1118},{"type":16,"tag":21,"props":1125,"children":1126},{},[1127],{"type":25,"value":1128},"This code creates a basic Express server that listens on port 3000 and responds with \"Hello World!\" to HTTP GET requests to the root URL (/).",{"type":16,"tag":187,"props":1130,"children":1132},{"id":1131},"step-4-running-your-express-server",[1133],{"type":25,"value":1134},"Step 4: Running Your Express Server",{"type":16,"tag":21,"props":1136,"children":1137},{},[1138],{"type":25,"value":1139},"Run your server using Node.js:",{"type":16,"tag":48,"props":1141,"children":1144},{"className":1142,"code":1143,"language":1073,"meta":8},[1071],"Copy code\nnode app.js\nVisit http://localhost:3000 in your browser. You should see the message \"Hello World!\".\n",[1145],{"type":16,"tag":56,"props":1146,"children":1147},{"__ignoreMap":8},[1148],{"type":25,"value":1143},{"type":16,"tag":187,"props":1150,"children":1152},{"id":1151},"step-5-building-a-simple-api",[1153],{"type":25,"value":1154},"Step 5: Building a Simple API",{"type":16,"tag":21,"props":1156,"children":1157},{},[1158],{"type":25,"value":1159},"Now, let's expand our server to act as a simple API. For example, let's create an endpoint that returns a list of users.",{"type":16,"tag":21,"props":1161,"children":1162},{},[1163],{"type":25,"value":1164},"Add the following code to your app.js:",{"type":16,"tag":48,"props":1166,"children":1169},{"className":1167,"code":1168,"language":946,"meta":8},[944],"const users = [{ name: 'Alice' }, { name: 'Bob' }]\n\napp.get('/users', (req, res) => {\n  res.json(users)\n})\n",[1170],{"type":16,"tag":56,"props":1171,"children":1172},{"__ignoreMap":8},[1173],{"type":25,"value":1168},{"type":16,"tag":21,"props":1175,"children":1176},{},[1177,1179,1187],{"type":25,"value":1178},"Now, if you visit ",{"type":16,"tag":1180,"props":1181,"children":1185},"a",{"href":1182,"rel":1183},"http://localhost:3000/users",[1184],"nofollow",[1186],{"type":25,"value":1182},{"type":25,"value":1188},", you will see the JSON representation of the users array.",{"type":16,"tag":187,"props":1190,"children":1192},{"id":1191},"step-6-testing-your-api",[1193],{"type":25,"value":1194},"Step 6: Testing Your API",{"type":16,"tag":21,"props":1196,"children":1197},{},[1198],{"type":25,"value":1199},"It’s important to test your API. You can use tools like Postman or curl to test your endpoints.",{"type":16,"tag":187,"props":1201,"children":1203},{"id":1202},"step-7-next-steps",[1204],{"type":25,"value":1205},"Step 7: Next Steps",{"type":16,"tag":21,"props":1207,"children":1208},{},[1209],{"type":25,"value":1210},"From here, you can start building more complex APIs. Consider the following:",{"type":16,"tag":21,"props":1212,"children":1213},{},[1214],{"type":25,"value":1215},"Implementing CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operations.\nConnecting your API to a database.\nAdding authentication and authorization.\nOrganizing your code with routers and controllers.",{"type":16,"tag":187,"props":1217,"children":1218},{"id":143},[1219],{"type":25,"value":146},{"type":16,"tag":21,"props":1221,"children":1222},{},[1223],{"type":25,"value":1224},"Express.js simplifies the process of building APIs in Node.js. It's a great starting point for developers looking to delve into backend development. With its minimalist approach, you have the freedom to structure your applications as you see fit, making Express.js an invaluable tool in your development toolkit.",{"title":8,"searchDepth":153,"depth":153,"links":1226},[1227,1228,1229,1230,1231,1232,1233,1234,1235],{"id":1043,"depth":153,"text":1046},{"id":1054,"depth":153,"text":1057},{"id":1086,"depth":153,"text":1089},{"id":1106,"depth":153,"text":1109},{"id":1131,"depth":153,"text":1134},{"id":1151,"depth":153,"text":1154},{"id":1191,"depth":153,"text":1194},{"id":1202,"depth":153,"text":1205},{"id":143,"depth":153,"text":146},"content:1.writings:building-your-first-api-with-expressjs-a-beginners-guide.md","1.writings/building-your-first-api-with-expressjs-a-beginners-guide.md","1.writings/building-your-first-api-with-expressjs-a-beginners-guide",1727401987681]